Laparoscopic cholecysto-jejunostomy for obstructing pancreatic cancer: technique and report of two cases. Laparoscopic cholecysto-jejunostomy was performed on two patients with obstructive jaundice due to a mass in the head of the pancreas. Diagnostic studies included CT scan, ERCP, arteriogram, and percutaneous needle aspiration cytology. Both patients recovered without event and were discharged after 4 days.